{
  "body": "You are designing a cinematic fantasy character portrait.\n\nCONTENT BRIEF\n- Character: {{character}}\n- Setting: {{setting}}\n- Copy: {{copy}}\n\nSTYLE DIRECTION\n- Genre / medium: Cinematic fantasy illustration with photorealistic rendering\n- Composition: Portrait orientation (3:2 aspect ratio), mid-close framing with the character filling the center of the composition. Dynamic pose emphasizing action and emotion.\n- Lens / camera: Wide aperture lens (f/1.8) for shallow depth of field, with soft bokeh and natural perspective compression.\n- Lighting: Diffuse soft light with a warm golden backlight and cool ambient fill. Subsurface scattering visible on skin and glowing accents on props.\n- Color palette and grading: Neutral tones with accents of vibrant teal and gold. Graded for cinematic drama with high contrast and subtle desaturation.\n- Texture / surface: Hyper-detailed textures on surfaces like metallic armor, glowing weaponry, and fabric. Slightly glossy highlights enhance realism.\n- Post-processing: Subtle bloom, halation around glowing elements, moderate vignette, and lens flare effects.\n- Mood: Dramatic, heroic, intense, and immersive.\n- References: Inspired by Blizzard Entertainment's cinematics, Unreal Engine renders, and the visual storytelling of titles like Final Fantasy and Elden Ring.\n- Mood adjustment: {{mood}}\n\nDESIGN RULES\n- Aspect: 2:3 portrait (~1024×1536) suitable for promotional posters or character art.\n- Ensure glowing elements have a soft gradient and blend naturally with the surrounding lighting.\n- Maintain the focal point on the character's face and key props (e.g., weapon).\n\nAVOID\n- Overly saturated colors that clash with the cinematic tone\n- Flat lighting without depth or drama\n- Busy backgrounds that distract from the character\n- Unrealistic proportions or exaggerated caricature\n- Harsh shadows or sharp transitions\n\nAdditional constraints: {{extra}}\n\n——————\nCharacter: {{character}}\nSetting: {{setting}}\nCopy: {{copy}}\nMood adjustment: {{mood}}\nExtra notes: {{extra}}",
